00679 
00681 class SimTkProfile {
00682     public:
00684         enum Feature {              // (byte-1)*8 + (bitno-1)
00686             MenuSelection =         (1-1)*8 + (4-1), 
00688             UCS2EntrySupported =    (2-1)*8 + (6-1), 
00690             UCS2DisplaySupported =  (2-1)*8 + (7-1), 
00692             DisplayExtensionText =  (2-1)*8 + (8-1), 
00694             BinaryChoiceGetInkey =  (8-1)*8 + (4-1), 
00696             ScreenSizingParameters =(14-1)*8 +(8-1), 
00698             VariableSizeFontSupport=(15-1)*8 +(8-1), 
00700             DisplayResizable =      (16-1)*8 +(1-1), 
00702             TextWrapping =          (16-1)*8 +(2-1), 
00704             TextScrolling =         (16-1)*8 +(3-1), 
00706             WidthReductionInAMenu = (16-1)*8 +(8-1), 
00707 
00708             // to be continued on request
00709         };
00710 
00711         SimTkProfile(const T_PROFILE & profile) : m_profile(profile) { }
00712 
00713         SimTkProfile(const SimTkProfile & profile) : m_profile(profile.m_profile) { }
00714 
00715         SimTkProfile() { memset((void*)&m_profile,0x00,sizeof(m_profile)); }
00716 
00717         const T_PROFILE & GetProfile() const { return m_profile; }
00718 
00719         void SetNumberOfCharsSupportedInDisplay(UINT8 no) {
00720             m_profile.data.A[13] = (m_profile.data.A[13] & 0xE0) + (no & 0x1F);
00721         }
00722 
00723         void SetNumberOfCharsAcrossDisplay(UINT8 no) {
00724             m_profile.data.A[14] = (m_profile.data.A[14] & 0x80) + (no & 0x7F);
00725         }
00726 
00727         void SetFeature(Feature no, BOOLEAN set = TRUE) {
00728             INT byteno = no / 8;
00729             UINT8 pbyte = m_profile.data.A[byteno];
00730             UINT8 mask = 1 << (no - (byteno*8));
00731             pbyte = set ? (pbyte | mask) : (pbyte & ~mask);
00732             m_profile.data.A[byteno] = pbyte; 
00733         }
00734 
00735     private:
00736         T_PROFILE m_profile;
00737 
00738 }; // SimTkTransactionId
